* replication, metadata servers are completely independent, the
  publisher is the real master and is responsible for replicating it's
  data on the whole cluster

* global namespace. The metadata server's hello message contains the
  cluster config that specifies all the servers in the local cluster
  as well as the server's position in the global namespace, and the
  delegations one level up. Delegations down are dealt with as
  referrals. Hello will need a ttl.
